@NODE "DownLoad" "What is this stuff?"

                             @{fg shine}What is this stuff?@{fg text}
 
 The original archive should contain the following files:
 
 @{fg fill}@{"Icons (dir)" LINK "Icons"}
 @{"Images (dir)" LINK "Images"}
 @{"WBStartup (dir)" LINK "WBStartup"}@{fg text}
 DirectoryOpus.info               @{b}DOpus5Icons@{ub}
 DOpus5Icons.info                 @{b}DOpusScreen.pic@{ub}
 DOpusScreen.pic.info             @{b}MWB_DOpus5.guide@{ub}
 MWB_DOpus5.guide.info            

 The @{b}DOpus5Icons@{ub} is just a picture of everything in the @{"images drawer" LINK "Images"} as well
 as well as some extra stuff (it's handy as a template for drawing your own,
 but if you do, make sure you upload them for everyone else to enjoy!)
 
 @{b}DOpusScreen.pic@{ub} is a snapshot of my DOpus screen which may give you some
 ideas!
 
 @{b}MWB_DOpus5.guide@{ub} - you are reading it ;)
@ENDNODE
 
@NODE "Icons" "Icons"
@TOC "Download"

                                     @{fg shine}Icons@{fg text}
  
 This archive contains the following icons:
  
  AppIcon.info                     Buttons.info
  Environment.info                 Filetype.info
  Group.info                       Lister.info
  Settings.info                    

 I realize that these may look identical to the ones supplied with DOpus, but
 they have been fixed. The original icons @{i}swim@{ui} when you click on them - there
 were gliches in them which I fixed (I don't know why - it just bugged me I 
 guess!?! ;)
@ENDNODE
  
