                                   @{fg shine}WBStartup@{fg text}
 
 This archive includes the following items in the WBStartup drawer:
  
   Opus5_Startup                    Opus5_Startup.info
 
 I've just put this here, because I think that the icon I drew for the
 Opus5_Startup is better than the one which is provided (you may not?).
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "System Requirements..."
                            
                            @{fg shine}System Requirements...@{fg text}
 
 I believe DOpus5 requires OS2.0+, but you may use this stuff on any Amiga (but
 in order to get a 3 bitplane @{"MWB" LINK "MWB"} atmosphere on OS1.2-1.3, you will need
 MagicWB1.3 written by Cléo Saulnier in pix/icon on Aminet).
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"

                                 @{fg shine}Installation@{fg text}

 If I knew how to write an installation script I'd have included one...all you
 need to do is copy this stuff where you want it. One recommendation, however
 would be to rename the images drawer in DOpus5: to something else and then
 copy the included images drawer into DOpus5: (since this is where DOpus looks
 for icons be default).

 As for the @{"pictures and the guide" LINK "DownLoad"}, you can delete them when you're done with
 them (although you might like to hang on to the @{"DOpus5Icons picture" LINK "DownLoad"} which
 serves as a good template for drawing your own icons and an index when you're
 not sure which icon to pick).
@ENDNODE

@NODE "HintsTips" "Hints & Tips & HELP!"
@NEXT "HintsTips"

                             @{fg shine}Hints & Tips & HELP!@{fg fill}

 · If you decide to use the included toolbar icons, it is a good idea to delete
   or rename the @{b}default images drawer@{ub} in @{b}DOpus5:@{ub}. Then copy the @{"Images" LINK "Images"} drawer
   included in this archive into your @{b}DOpus5:@{ub} directory (since this is where
   DOpus looks for images by default).
   
 · If you want to make a drive bank (similar to DOpus4) you can use a button
   bank with the @{b}ScanDir@{ub} command (see my @{"DOpusScreen.pic" LINK "DownLoad"}).
@{fg text}
 · Is it possible to have drives (icons on the DOpus screen which do not
   necessarily exist on WorkBench? For instance, for an assign? 
 
 · Is everyone having the same problems I am with snapshoting icons in DOpus..
   wherever you snapshot the windows in DOpus is where they end up on the
   workbench? Am I doing something wrong?
@{fg fill} 
   -> Answered by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}: Yes, there is currently no way around this :(
@{fg text}     
 · What the hell happened to the SWAPDIR and COPYDIR commands? Is there a way
   to impliment this through other commands (to operate on the source and the
   destination)?
 
 · Does it annoy anyone else that when you click on the button banks that they
   remain highlighted and then you have to go back and click on the window?
   Once the operation has been preformed, the window in which the action was
   preformed should be rehighlighted...right?
 
 · Can you save the prefs so that the clock remains ON?
@{fg fill}
   -> Answered by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}: Yes, but you must quit DOpus for the changes to
      remain in effect.
@{fg text}        
 · I wish you could get rid of the borders on the button banks...what a waste
   of space!
 
 · How do you replace the cycle gadget in the ToolBarLister?
@{fg fill} 
   -> Answered by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}: See @{"Images" LINK "Images"} - at the bottom of the page, there
      is a note on how to replace the cycle gadget.

 · Here another good tip from @{"Leo" LINK "Author"}: @{"How to add an LHA Dest. file requester" LINK "LHA"}
@{fg text} 
 · I haven't got time to write any more.
@{fg fill} 
 If you have answers for any of these @{"I'd love to hear from you" LINK "Author"}.
@ENDNODE

